  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Lupus disease is characterized by the production of pathogenic autoantibodies, which
      participate in end-organ damages. The phenotype of B cells producing the pathogenic
      autoantibodies in lupus patients is today unknown. Antinucleosome antibodies are
      characteristic of lupus disease.This project proposes to detect antinucleosome B cells in
      lupus patients and to analyse their phenotype and their frequency.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
