    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion criteria for SLE patients:

        SLE patient : diagnostic based on ACR criteria

          -  SLE patient producing seric anti-nucleosome antibodies (ELISA)

          -  SLEDAI-2K activity score : inferior to 5 for quiescent patients, superior to 8 since
             at least 2 months for active patients

        Exclusion criteria for SLE patients:

        -- Other autoimmune diseases than SLE- Induced lupus

          -  Treatment with corticosteroids &gt;10mg/d (prednisone) for quiescent patients

          -  Treatment with corticosteroids &gt;20mg/d (prednisone) for active patients

          -  Oral immunosuppressive treatment during the last 6 months (methotrexate,
             azathioprine, ciclosporine, mycophénolate mofétil) for all patients, treatment during
             the last year with cyclophosphamide or monoclonal antibodies (rituximab, belimumab)
             for pour quiescent patients

          -  Disease which can modify B and T lymphocyte functions: primary immune deficiencies,
             evolutive infections, chronic viral infection (VIH in particular), chemotherapy or
             neoplasm antecedent
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
